androidx.test.internal.runner.listener

Class InstrumentationResultPrinter

  • java.lang.Object
    • RunListener
      • androidx.test.internal.runner.listener.InstrumentationRunListener
        • androidx.test.internal.runner.listener.InstrumentationResultPrinter

  • public class InstrumentationResultPrinter
extends InstrumentationRunListener
    A RunListener that sends detailed pass/fail results back as instrumentation status bundles.

    When running instrumentation in '-r' or raw mode, output will be displayed in this format 

         INSTRUMENTATION_STATUS: key=value
    for each key-value pair in the bundle.

    When running in normal aka non raw mode, only the value of the Instrumentation.REPORT_KEY_STREAMRESULT key will be displayed.

Generated javadoc for the new package structure to make it clearer which packages are bundled with the Android operating system, and which are packaged with your app's APK. Going forward, the android.* package hierarchy will be reserved for Android packages that ship with the operating system; other packages will be issued in the new androidx.* package hiearchy.
